<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40167c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40167c">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40167c"> 167(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> kurbash </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Floggings, beatings, the <i>kurbash</i>, a whip, typically of hippopotamus hide, and the bastinado, a cane for whipping the soles of the feet, were part and parcel of the British administrative system in the early nineteenth century in Egypt and the Sudan. It was not the least unusual to hear of people being beaten to death in an effort, for example, to extract taxes or to discover runaway recruits. </mm> </dd></dl>
